OL,6,FHSE inspector David Beaton, said:
OL,7,F"This was a tragic and preventable
OL,8,Fdeath. Mr Keegan was placed at undue
OL,9,Frisk by operating a machine with
OL,10,Funderlying maintenance defects, which
OL,11,Fhe would have been unaware of when
OL,12,Fattempting to reverse the forklift in
OL,13,Fthe dark onto a trailer with an
OL,14,Fexposed edge.
OL,16,F"Had Mr Keegan been wearing the
OL,17,Fseatbelt provided, the accident he
OL,18,Fsuffered would likely not have proven
OL,19,Ffatal.
